{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Delhi", "text_new": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Delhi, India}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{update|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| map1            = Location map India Delhi EN.svg\n| legend1         = {{legend|#d40000ff|Confirmed cases reported}}\n| image           = Jobless migrant workers at Delhi during lockdown IMG 20200414 144754.jpg\n| caption         = Keeping social distance jobless migrant workers at Delhi at a que for free lunch during lockdown on 14 April 2020\n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Delhi]], [[India]]\n| first_case      = 2 March 2020\n| arrival_date    = \n| origin          = [[China]]\n| confirmed_cases = 1707<ref>{{cite web |title=MoHFW {{!}} Home |url=https://www.mohfw.gov.in/ |website=mohfw |accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = \n|active_cases     = 1551\n| recovery_cases  = 51\n| deaths          = 42\n| website         =\n}}\n\nThe '''[[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]]''' was confirmed in the Indian state of [[Delhi]] and the state has been under lockdown along with the country. First case was reported on 2 March 2020. Total infected people reported as on 17 April 2020 is 1640 consisting of 38 deaths.<ref>{{citation |title=Coronavirus latest updates: India's testing ratio not low, says ICMR|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/coronavirus-latest-updates-delhi-maharashtra-report-dip-in-new-cases/articleshow/75171925.cms|work=[[Times Of India]]|date=16 April 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Here's a quick read on the COVID-19 related updates:|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-cases-in-india-live-news-latest-updates-april15/liveblog/75150277.cms|work=[[The Economic Times]]|date=16 April 2020 }}</ref>\nAs of 6 March 2020 all primary schools were closed  Delhi Govt till 31 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus threat: Delhi govt orders closure of all primary schools till March 31 |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/education/coronavirus-threat-delhi-govt-orders-closure-of-all-primary-schools-till-march-31/story-ExewEmJeLCZ6egWDW6Ss2N.html |accessdate=5 March 2020 |work=Hindustan Times |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306042604/https://www.hindustantimes.com/education/coronavirus-threat-delhi-govt-orders-closure-of-all-primary-schools-till-march-31/story-ExewEmJeLCZ6egWDW6Ss2N.html |archive-date=6 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On the same day in fear of [[COVID-19]], [[Fashion Design Council of India]] had postpone their show till further notice.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indulgexpress.com/fashion/2020/mar/06/fdci-postpones-lotus-makeup-india-fashion-week-amidst-covid-19-fears-22914.html|title=FDCI postpones Lotus Makeup India Fashion Week amidst COVID-19 fears|work=Indulge Express|accessdate=7 March 2020}}</ref> The [[2020 ISSF World Cup]] has been postponed which was scheduled to be held in May 2020.<ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/sports/virus-hits-indian-sports/articleshow/74519560.cms|title=Virus hits Indian sports|date=6 March 2020|work=Economic Times|accessdate=7 March 2020|url-status=live|agency=PTI}}</ref> On 14 March 2020 [[Badminton World Federation]] (BWF) had also postpone their all tournaments due to same reason.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/sports-news-coronavirus-india-open-badminton-tournament-cancelled/348760|title=Coronavirus: India Open Badminton Tournament Cancelled|last=|first=|date=14 March 2020|website=Outlook|agency=PTI|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThousands of migrants from [[Uttar Pradesh]] and [[Bihar]] gathered in Anand Vihar Bus Station on 29 March 2020.<ref>{{citation |title=Coronavirus: Stranded migrant workers throng Delhi bus terminal in effort to get back home |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/migrant-worker-delhi-up-border-buses-coronavirus-community-spread-1660822-2020-03-29 |work=[[India Today]] |date=29 March 2020 }}</ref> More than 200 people from a religious gathering in Alami Markaz Banglewali Masjid in Nizamuddin area were quarantined after suspected contact with infected people.1300 tabligi were found stuck including foreigins in Markaz.<ref>{{citation |title=Covid-19: 200 quarantined, contact tracing on after Delhi mosque gathering |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/police-cordon-off-part-of-nizamuddin-after-people-show-covid-19-symptoms/story-ChOXzLNx3mSl490JgyqvKK.html |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=30 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Gross act of negligence: Delhi govt assures action against Nizamuddin Markaz that put over 500 in danger of Covid-19 |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/gross-act-negligence-delhi-govt-action-against-nizamuddin-markaz-gathering-covid19-coronavirus-1661507-2020-03-30 |work=[[India Today]] |date=30 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Coronavirus: 10 deaths, 300 hospitalisations linked to Tablighi Jamaat meet in Nizamuddin |url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/coronavirus-10-deaths-300-hospitalisations-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-meet/articleshow/74902930.cms |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=31 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nIt was reported that air quality index of Delhi improved on 28 March 2020 after the lockdown and reduced vehicular movements.<ref>{{citation |title=Corona blue: Clear skies, clean air in Delhi |url=https://m.timesofindia.com/city/delhi/corona-blue-clear-skies-clean-air/articleshow/74855039.cms |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/India/Delhi medical cases chart}}\n\n==Government responses==\n===March===\n\n====Travel and entry restrictions====\nChief minister [[Arvind Kejriwal]] announced that from 23 to 31 March 2020, all domestic/international flights arriving to [[Delhi]] would be suspended.<ref name=\"EcoTimes23March\"/>\n\n===Lockdown===\n* '''22 March'''\n:*Arvind Kejriwal had announced [[lockdown]] from 23 March 6 a.m. to 31 March midnight. Except essential services every services had been closed due to [[COVID-19]] pandemic. Borders had been sealed except for transportation of essential services.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus in Delhi: CM Kejriwal announces lockdown from March 23 to 31|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-in-delhi-cm-kejriwal-announces-lockdown-from-march-23-to-31/videoshow/74761871.cms|accessdate=18 April 2020 |work=The Economic Times |date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n* '''24 March'''\n:*Lockdown further extended till 14 April 2020 after PM [[Narendra Modi]] announced a complete nationwide lockdown, starting from midnight of 24 March 2020 for 21 days.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.firstpost.com/health/narendra-modi-on-coronavirus-speech-live-updates-streaming-watch-india-pm-address-to-nation-on-covid-19-today-latest-news-lockdown-janata-curfew-8182241.html|title=Narendra Modi on Coronavirus Outbreak LIVE Updates: India under complete shutdown for 21 days starting 12 pm tonight, says PM|date=|work=The Firstpost|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*'''14 April'''\n:*Modi extended lockdown  till 3 May 2020.<ref name=\"lockdownext\">\n{{cite news |first1=Utpal|last1=Bhaskar|title=PM Modi announces extension of lockdown till 3 May | url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/pm-modi-announces-extension-of-lockdown-till-3-may-11586839412073.html |work=The Livemint |date=14 April 2020}}\n</ref> after recommendation from several state governments.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Rounak|last1=Jain|url=https://www.businessinsider.in/india/news/lockdown-in-telangana-extended-till-june-3/articleshow/75014509.cms|title=Telangana CM suggests lockdown extension by two weeks|date=|work=The Business Insder|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date= 6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Impact==\n===Commercial establishments===\nOn 19 March, Arvind Kejriwal announced that all restaurants will be closed till 31 March in view of the ever increasing case of coronavirus. He said that there will be a take away system from restaurants without any eating facilities in the venue. He also said that 20 or more people will not be allowed to unite anywhere in the state.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kejriwal govt orders Delhi restaurants to shut shop with immediate effect until 31 March| url=https://theprint.in/india/kejriwal-govt-orders-delhi-restaurants-to-shut-shop-with-immediate-effect-until-31-march/384034/|website=theprint|author=}}</ref>\nAll shops, industries,  commercial establishments, offices  shall be closed.<ref name=\"EcoTimes23March\">{{cite news |title=Coronavirus Fallout: Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal announces lockdown until March 31 |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-fallout-delhi-cm-arvind-kejriwal-announces-lockdown-until-march-31/articleshow/74761137.cms |accessdate=17 April 2020 |publisher=The Economic Times |date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==State government response==\nDelhi government had initiated a disinfection drive in Delhi from 13 April 2020<ref>{{citation |title=Covid-19: Delhi govt to sanitise city's red, orange zones from Monday, says Arvind Kejriwal|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/covid-19-delhi-govt-to-sanitise-city-s-red-orange-zones-from-monday-says-arvind-kejriwal-1666196-2020-04-12|work=[[India Today]] |date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n[[File:Delhi Govt disinfection drive during COVID-19 pandemic in DelhiVID 20200416 132044.webm|thumb|Delhi Govt disinfection drive during COVID-19 pandemic in Delhi]]\n\n=== Help ===\n\n====Ration====\n*'''4 April,''' as per CM [[Arvind Kejriwal|Arvind Kejriwal's]] announcement people who dont have ration card can avail free ration from fair price shop.<ref>{{citation|title=People-without-Ration-Cards-in-Delhi-can-now-avail-free-ration-from-Fair-Price-Shops|url=http://newsonair.com/News?title=People-without-Ration-Cards-in-Delhi-can-now-avail-free-ration-from-Fair-Price-Shops%3A-Delhi-govt&id=384700|work=News On Air|date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n*'''5 April''',  out of 71 lakh ration card holder in Delhi 60% had received ration.<ref name=\"ration\">{{citation|title=Delhi: 60% of 71 lakh people under PDS given ration, those without cards can fill forms|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/delhi/delhi-60-of-71-lakh-people-under-pds-given-ration-those-without-cards-can-fill-forms-6347808/|work=[[Indian Express]]|date=5 April 2020}}</ref> As per CM till 5 April 50,000 to 60,000 people hv applied for coupon to avail 5&nbsp;kg of wheat, rice and sugar, free of cost and who don't have ration card.<ref  name=\"ration\"/> Some people complained about distribution, in a video conference with area MLAs including other party, CM requested that they should reach out to people in distress and help them register to avail ration.<ref  name=\"ration\"/>\n\n=== Hotspot ===\n[[File:Minister visiting the Coronavirus Quarantine Centre 2.jpg|thumb|The Minister of State for Home Affairs, [[Nityanand Rai]] visiting evacuees at the Coronavirus Quarantine Centre, after completion of their requisite quarantine period, at the ITBP Chhawla Centre, in New Delhi on 13 March 2020.]]\nOn 14 April 2020 after adding eight new hotspots, now total hotspot numbers are 55 in Delhi.<ref>{{citation |title=Coronavirus lockdown: 8 more hotspots in Delhi, 55 areas sealed in Delhi|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-lockdown-8-more-hotspots-in-delhi-55-areas-sealed-in-delhi-check-full-list-here-1667005-2020-04-14|work=[[India Today]]|date=14 April 2020 }}</ref> On 15 April 2020 after adding two more places, total hotspot numbers are 57.<ref name=15AprilIndiaToday>{{citation |title=Coronavirus: Delhi adds 2 areas in containment zone list, city tally rises to 1,578|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/complete-list-of-57-coronavirus-containment-zones-in-delhi-1667371-2020-04-15|work=[[India Today]]|date=15 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n=== SHIELD plan ===\nThe Delhi Government announced operation SHIELD in order to curb the spread of the virus in the containment zones or the hotspots. It is a six layers plan, where S refers to sealing the immediate area, H refers to home quarantine to all people living in the area, I refers to isolation and contact tracing of people, E refers to essential supply of commodities, L refers to local sanitization and D refers to door to door helth check of people in the area.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Delhi govt announces Operation SHIELD to take on COVID-19 |url=https://www.businesstoday.in/latest/trends/coronavirus-delhi-govt-announces-operation-shield-to-take-on-covid-19/story/400648.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=The Business Today |date=10 April 2020}}</ref> The first success of the operation came from Dilshad Garden, an area where the virus was widely spreaded. The Dlehi Government annoucned on 10 April, that the operation SHIELD was successful in containing the spread of the virus in this area. The state Health Minister, [[Satyendra Kumar Jain|Satyendra Jain]] said that the area was virus-free after the implentation of the six layer operation.<ref>{{cite news |title=Operation SHIELD successful in containing COVID-19 spread in Dilshad Garden: Delhi health minister |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/healthcare/biotech/healthcare/operation-shield-successful-in-containing-covid-19-spread-in-dilshad-garden-delhi-health-minister/articleshow/75082473.cms?from=mdr |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=The Economic Times |date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Cases ==\n=== Cases by districts ===\n{{updated|17 April 2020}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Administrative district wise +ve cases<ref>{{cite web |title=State/District wise Details of COVID-19 positive cases |url=https://www.mohfw.gov.in/pdf/Districtreporting408.pdf |publisher=Govt. of India (MoHFW) |accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n! District !! Number of cases\n|-\n| Central Delhi || 75\n|-\n| East Delhi DELHI || 30\n|-\n| New Delhi || 26\n|-\n| North Delhi || 24\n|-\n| North-East Delhi || 15\n|-\n| North-West Delhi || 14\n|-\n| Shahadara  || 37\n|-\n| South Delhi || 62\n|-\n| South-East Delhi|| 65\n|-\n| South-West Delhi || 20\n|-\n| West Delhi || 49\n|-\n|  TJ from Quarantine  || 1080\n|-\n|  Others non traceable  || 143\n|-\n| TOTAL  || 1640\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus lockdown in India]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by city|Delhi]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India by state or union territory|Delhi]]\n[[Category:2020s in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Health in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Disasters in Delhi]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Delhi, India}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{update|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| map1            = Location map India Delhi EN.svg\n| legend1         = {{legend|#d40000ff|Confirmed cases reported}}\n| image           = Jobless migrant workers at Delhi during lockdown IMG 20200414 144754.jpg\n| caption         = Keeping social distance jobless migrant workers at Delhi at a que for free lunch during lockdown on 14 April 2020\n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Delhi]], [[India]]\n| first_case      = 2 March 2020\n| arrival_date    = \n| origin          = [[China]]\n| confirmed_cases = 1707<ref>{{cite web |title=MoHFW {{!}} Home |url=https://www.mohfw.gov.in/ |website=mohfw |accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = \n|active_cases     = 1551\n| recovery_cases  = 51\n| deaths          = 42\n| website         =\n}}\n\nThe '''[[201